==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|additivus|lang=la}}, from the participial stem of {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|addere||to add|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈadɪtɪv/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæɾətɪv/|/ˈæɾəɾɪv/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} Pertaining to [[addition]]; that can be, or has been, [[added]].
# {{context|mathematics|of a [[function]], etc.|lang=en}} [[distributive#English|Distributive]] over [[addition]].
#: ''Matrix multiplication is '''additive''' in that <math>M\vec v+M\vec w=M(\vec v+\vec w)</math>.''
# {{context|algebra|lang=en}} Having [[addition]] as an [[operator]].
#: ''It is natural to look at a finite cyclic group as an '''additive''' group.''
# {{context|chemistry|lang=en}} Pertaining to chemical [[addition]].
# {{context|genetics|lang=en}} Describing [[gene]]s (or the interaction etc. of such genes) which govern the same trait and whose effects work together on the [[phenotype]].

====Antonyms====
* [[subtractive]]

